BRIEFLY 
Paramount Deal for Children's Book Author: Paramount Pictures has purchased 
exclusive rights to the works of author and illustrator Richard Scarry. 
Sidney Ganis, president of the motion picture group, said Paramount expects to 
use his works in film and other areas. Scarry has sold more than 100 million 
books in 30 languages worldwide. His best-known characters include "Lowly 
Worm," "Mr. Frumble the Pig" and "Huckle Cat." 
